Description: The increasing availability of large clinico-genomic datasets generated through routine cancer care affords the opportunity to conduct precision oncology research using observational data at scale. This session will provide an overview of multi-institutional clinico-genomic collaboratives in the United States and Japan, with attention to analytical challenges that arise from real-world patterns of genomic data collection.
